			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm a lvl 41 gnome necro on Maelin, first character so I guess that makes me a newb.
<br />

<br />
Yes, tanking would be an answer, but I'm looking for recommendations on being able to do it rather quickly and safely, or at least as quickly as possible, without actually buying points in it.
<br />

<br />
This is my first character and I've recently read that it's pretty important for necs to have some ok melee stats at higher levels just in case.  I, sadly, have horrible melee stats and just made lv 41.
<br />

<br />
Piercing = 41 and Offence = 66.  I have been tanking in groups a bit just to try to raise my numbers, but it's painfully slow, slower than raising any other stats I have.  I've been using <a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=684" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stiletto of the Bloodclaw</a> and it procs about 150 times more frequently than I get a skillup.  It's not a particularly great weapon, but I love the effect and the price was right, and prices in the bazaar are quite high.
<br />

<br />
I thought I had a great idea, I know in Steamfront there's this clockwork by the mino cave that has huge hit points and never attacks back, so I thought I'd get a DMF and tank him to raise piercing skills.  Guess what, not a single skillup after a half hour.
<br />

<br />
So what gives?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
